node.title: Grieving relatives left furious after St Basil's managers refuse to speak at inquest into deadly outbreak
node.description: Managers of St Basil's aged care home at the centre of Australia's deadliest COVID-19 outbreak refuse to give evidence during an inquest into the tragedy.

node.title: Late Night Praises Fox News Hosts for Their Acting Skills
node.description: The news that Fox News anchors sent texts on Jan. 6 urging President Trump to speak out against the insurrection while blaming antifa on air was the talk of late night on Tuesday.

node.title: Energy Australia charged over worker's power station death
node.description: WorkSafe has charged Energy Australia with three breaches of the Occupational Health and Safety Act over the 2018 death of Graeme Edwards, who was fatally burnt while working at the Latrobe Valley power station.

node.title: China critic forms new political party with young, diverse candidates ahead of federal election
node.description: Five people, mostly in their twenties, are part of the "same political movement" and hope to run in the 2022 federal election under the banner of a new political party.

node.title: Alex Braes inquest told the teen's ability to cope with pain from infected toenail made it hard to assess him
node.description: The inquest into the death of the Broken Hill teenager Alex Braes, who was turned away from hospital three times before he died, has heard he was conscious and speaking to staff and was "compensating for the sepsis until he couldn't".

node.title: 'It's quite outrageous': Luxon calls for accountability over emergency housing rentals
node.description: National Party leader Christopher Luxon says blaming a spending of $37m on inflated rentals for emergency accommodation on an "operational decision" is being used as cover to not be accountable. Audio

node.title: NSW Covid-19 cases jump to 10-week high as unvaccinated 'freedom day' looms
node.description: NSW will press ahead with plans to give a swathe of freedoms to unvaccinated people tomorrow, as the number of new daily Covid-19 infections rose to a 10-week high.

node.title: Attempts to fix Transmission Gully made it worse, reports show
node.description: An engineering consultancy firm said the problems should be addressed before the road opened to the public, particularly with the summer months ahead.

node.title: Your Wednesday Briefing
node.description: Results from Pfizer’s Covid pill.

node.title: South Australia records highest daily COVID-19 total since April 2020, as international quarantine time cut
node.description: South Australia records 25 new cases of COVID-19, the highest daily total since April 2020. The Premier says quarantine periods for international arrivals will reduce from 14 to seven days.

node.title: Patty Mills stars in Brooklyn Nets' overtime win against Toronto Raptors
node.description: Called up to start in a depleted Nets line-up, Mills scores a season-high 30 points in a thrilling 131-129 victory over the Raptors in New York.

node.title: The ACT government could soon be required to provide free period products in public places
node.description: Sanitary products would be accessible across the ACT to anyone who needs them under a new proposal to end period poverty in the territory.

node.title: TGA blocks bid to have MDMA, magic mushrooms as mental health treatments
node.description: Australia's medicines regulator rejects call to legalise psychedelic drugs for use in mental health settings, saying changing the rules could lead to the drugs being misused.

node.title: Days out from NT's borders reopening, COVID-19 rules change again. Here's what's happening
node.description: Can interstate travellers visit Kakadu National Park? Can essential workers return to work in a remote community after visiting family in Queensland? We answer your questions.

node.title: WA to tighten border with NSW as super-spreader events fuel 'very concerning' rise in COVID cases
node.description: On Saturday, Western Australia will reclassify NSW as an 'extreme risk' state, where 25,000 cases of COVID-19 a day is expected by the end of January.

node.title: Easing COVID mask restrictions at odds with NSW Health advice as infections surge
node.description: Publicly, it's been a united front for almost two years: NSW's top medico Kerry Chant standing beside a premier, who has proclaimed whatever COVID-19 decision they were making was "based on the health advice". Now, there's been a departure from that script.

node.title: Steel & Tube Holdings upgrades half-year earnings guidance
node.description: Steel & Tube Holdings' underlying profit was expected to be between $20 million and $22m in the half year to December.

node.title: Some N.F.L. Teams Face a Financial Cliff Despite Raised Salary Cap
node.description: The New Orleans Saints and Green Bay Packers, beset by hefty long-term contracts, will be forced into personnel decisions in 2022.

node.title: ‘The Music Man’ Once Had a Disabled Character. Then He Was Erased.
node.description: At the urging of producers, Meredith Willson cut a boy in a wheelchair from the early scripts for his 1957 musical. A look back shows what was lost.

node.title: The Year in Pictures 2021
node.description: While many people, fearing the virus, continued to stay close to home, photographers traveled the world, documenting the world‘s turmoil and triumphs.

node.title: Flooding and slips affecting motorists around the country
node.description: Heavy rain is causing slips and flooding around the country, affecting motorists across the regions.

node.title: 'Simply eating dinner felt like an intense workout': Reporter Charles Brice spent two weeks in hospital with COVID-19

node.title: Curry burns NBA 3-point record

node.title: Nelson resource consents delayed by council staff shortage

node.title: Wellington council allowed to strengthen quake-prone Toomath's Buildings - High Court

node.title: Lower North Island residents asked to watch out for wallabies

node.title: NASA probe is first spacecraft to enter the sun's atmosphere

node.title: Muslim Lawmaker Comes Under Fire in House Debate on ‘Islamophobia’
node.description: A conservative Republican accused Ilhan Omar, the sponsor of a House bill to combat anti-Muslim bias, of terrorist sympathies.

node.title: House Votes 222-208 to Hold Mark Meadows in Contempt of Congress
node.description: The House voted 222-208 to levy charges against the former Trump chief of staff.

node.title: Official confirms fireball from overturned petrol tanker kills 75 in Haiti
node.description: At least 75 people have died after a petrol tanker overturned and exploded in northern Haiti, unleashing a fireball that swept through homes and businesses.
